WEBVTT

00:49.216 --> 00:51.009
Hello, little girl.

00:53.512 --> 00:56.723
Would you like a scotchie?

00:59.059 --> 01:00.727
Oh...

01:00.811 --> 01:05.274
Such a sweet little girl.

01:11.196 --> 01:12.155
It's okay, pumpkin.

01:15.492 --> 01:16.827
Thank you.

01:17.452 --> 01:18.620
Come on, Alice.

01:18.704 --> 01:20.163
We need to get you
back to your room.

01:23.208 --> 01:25.043
Why did she call me a girl?

01:25.169 --> 01:26.753
It's okay. She's old.

01:26.879 --> 01:28.005
Probably confused.

01:28.046 --> 01:29.256
But I'm not a girl.

01:29.381 --> 01:30.424
I know you're not.

01:30.549 --> 01:32.593
You're also not a pumpkin,
but I still call you one.

02:09.254 --> 02:10.297
You did it?

02:11.256 --> 02:12.132
Yeah.

02:18.680 --> 02:19.973
It's gonna be okay.

02:20.766 --> 02:22.392
I know. I know.

02:22.476 --> 02:23.977
Can I see Grandpa now?

02:25.479 --> 02:26.813
Yeah.
Yeah, buddy.

02:26.897 --> 02:28.857
Uh, why don't you,
why don't you go in?

02:42.412 --> 02:44.456
<i>Santa Claus,</i>
<i>you're coming with us.</i>

02:44.581 --> 02:46.375
<i>No, you can't take him now.</i>

02:46.458 --> 02:47.334
<i>It's too near Christmas.</i>

02:47.459 --> 02:48.335
<i>Quiet, you.</i>

02:48.460 --> 02:49.461
<i>But--</i>

02:52.464 --> 02:54.758
<i>We don't want to hurt you,</i>
<i>Santa Claus,</i>

02:54.800 --> 02:56.635
<i>so come along quietly.</i>

02:58.303 --> 02:59.346
<i>Why?</i>

02:59.471 --> 03:02.140
<i>Why did you have to do that</i>
<i>to my helper?</i>

03:02.224 --> 03:03.141
<i>It's harmless.</i>

03:03.183 --> 03:04.601
<i>It'll wear off in a short while.</i>

03:04.685 --> 03:05.561
Grandpa?

03:06.228 --> 03:07.729
<i>Well, why didn't you say so</i>
<i>in the first place?</i>

03:07.729 --> 03:09.022
<i>Now you come with us.</i>

03:09.106 --> 03:10.649
<i>We need you on Mars.</i>

03:10.732 --> 03:11.733
Grandpa?

03:14.027 --> 03:16.280
<i>Are you sure this is Mars?</i>

03:16.363 --> 03:17.698
<i>Oh...</i>

03:17.781 --> 03:20.158
<i>I never saw</i>
<i>such lazy people,</i>

03:20.284 --> 03:22.119
<i>standing around like statues.</i>

03:23.120 --> 03:24.121
Grandpa?

03:25.497 --> 03:26.498
<i>Well?</i>

03:26.623 --> 03:28.834
<i>Earthlings Billy and Betty.</i>

03:30.335 --> 03:31.461
Billy.

03:31.503 --> 03:32.838
Come here, little boy.

03:35.340 --> 03:36.383
You've gotten so big.

03:36.508 --> 03:37.718
<i>There's someone else, too.</i>

03:37.843 --> 03:39.344
What have you been eating?

03:39.386 --> 03:40.721
Rocks?

03:40.846 --> 03:42.681
No, hamburgers.

03:42.764 --> 03:45.350
Do you like pickles
on your hamburgers?

03:47.227 --> 03:49.688
I love pickles
on my hamburgers.

03:50.397 --> 03:53.233
Pickles and-- and sauerkraut.

03:53.317 --> 03:54.526
Blegh!

03:55.110 --> 03:56.486
<i>Welcome, Santa Claus.</i>

03:56.570 --> 03:58.822
<i>We hope you'll make</i>
<i>the children on Mars very happy.</i>

03:59.323 --> 04:01.325
<i>I'll try, dear lady.</i>

04:01.450 --> 04:02.993
<i>I'll try.</i>

04:03.118 --> 04:04.828
Have you been a good boy?

04:06.121 --> 04:07.497
Good--

04:07.539 --> 04:10.876
Good boys get good things.

04:11.543 --> 04:13.879
What happens to boys
who aren't good?

04:15.589 --> 04:19.092
Naughty boys get punished.

04:20.385 --> 04:22.930
Santa is always watching.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.602
<i>Santa says I gotta fatten up.</i>

04:30.437 --> 04:32.022
Billy, water.

04:37.486 --> 04:40.239
<i>Now I'm Santa Claus.</i>

04:40.322 --> 04:41.615
Water.

04:48.497 --> 04:50.165
<i>Ho, ho, ho.</i>

04:50.249 --> 04:53.085
<i>Merry Christmas, everyone.</i>

05:16.108 --> 05:17.568
I mean, how was I supposed
to know

05:17.651 --> 05:19.236
it was going to happen
like that?

05:19.319 --> 05:20.487
How many did he have?

05:20.571 --> 05:22.197
Two, three, I--

05:22.281 --> 05:23.282
Was it two or three?

05:23.365 --> 05:24.908
I don't remember, okay?

05:25.534 --> 05:26.785
He must've reacted badly

05:26.869 --> 05:29.121
with those other meds
he had been taking. Shit.

05:29.246 --> 05:31.081
But he signed everything, right?

05:33.458 --> 05:34.751
Yeah.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.462
Is Grandpa gonna be okay?

05:38.255 --> 05:39.506
No, buddy.
Grandpa's dead.

05:39.631 --> 05:40.757
Geoffrey.

05:40.799 --> 05:42.217
What, do you want me
to lie to him?

05:42.301 --> 05:44.511
Yeah, a little tact
would be nice.

05:44.636 --> 05:46.471
So Grandpa's in heaven?

05:48.140 --> 05:51.018
Oh. Yes, pumpkin, he is.

06:03.655 --> 06:05.407
Come on, what are we
waiting for?

06:12.498 --> 06:13.665
Son of a bitch.

06:13.790 --> 06:14.666
Did he just hit us?

06:14.750 --> 06:15.667
Yeah!

06:16.293 --> 06:17.503
That's great.

06:17.628 --> 06:19.463
As if this night
couldn't get any worse.

06:19.505 --> 06:21.465
Merry Christmas, Chapman family.

06:21.507 --> 06:23.383
I'll look for the insurance.

06:31.266 --> 06:32.226
Great, yeah.

06:46.156 --> 06:47.241
Hey, pal.

06:47.324 --> 06:48.325
Look, I don't know
what happened,

06:48.367 --> 06:49.660
but clearly you hit me with...

06:53.121 --> 06:53.997
Geoffrey!

07:02.714 --> 07:04.007
Billy, get down!

07:14.184 --> 07:15.602
<i>Go back to bed, Billy.</i>

07:26.154 --> 07:28.323
<i>Santa Claus,</i>
<i>you're coming with us.</i>

07:28.407 --> 07:30.158
<i>No, you can't take him now.</i>

07:30.242 --> 07:31.368
<i>It's too near Christmas.</i>

07:31.410 --> 07:32.327
<i>Quiet, you!</i>

07:32.411 --> 07:33.412
<i>But...</i>

07:37.499 --> 07:38.959
<i>We don't want to hurt you,</i>

07:39.084 --> 07:41.587
<i>Santa Claus,</i>
<i>so come along quietly.</i>

07:50.762 --> 07:52.097
<i>Come on, kid.</i>

07:52.181 --> 07:55.267
<i>Do what you've got to do,</i>
<i>and then let's get out of here.</i>

07:55.350 --> 07:57.477
<i>This isn't our room.</i>

08:54.826 --> 08:59.832
<i>♪ So blue at Christmas ♪</i>

09:15.764 --> 09:17.850
Yo, Harold, you in there?

09:23.981 --> 09:25.691
I'll uh, go talk to the manager

09:25.774 --> 09:27.067
and see if he got a room.

09:27.693 --> 09:29.611
<i>I'm getting one</i>
<i>of those feelings.</i>

10:55.531 --> 10:56.740
Billy, get down!

11:20.639 --> 11:21.849
Hey!

11:48.292 --> 11:50.002
<i>I could use some coffee.</i>

11:52.296 --> 11:53.338
Yeah.

11:55.174 --> 11:56.175
Yeah, me too.

12:02.347 --> 12:03.432
<i>Sure you don't want</i>

12:03.515 --> 12:04.766
<i>to look around?</i>

12:05.309 --> 12:06.268
No.

12:06.351 --> 12:07.936
<i>Small towns have</i>
<i>a lot of secrets.</i>

12:08.020 --> 12:10.147
Good morning.
Coffee?

12:10.230 --> 12:12.065
Uh, yeah.
Yes, please.

12:16.278 --> 12:18.864
Um, where are we?

12:18.947 --> 12:19.907
Thunderbird.

12:19.990 --> 12:21.825
No, no, no. The, uh--
What town?

12:21.867 --> 12:22.868
Hackett.

12:22.993 --> 12:24.369
<i>Hackett?</i>

12:24.494 --> 12:25.787
<i>I like the sound of that.</i>

12:26.705 --> 12:27.831
I'll give you a minute.

12:30.709 --> 12:32.211
<i>You may be right.</i>

12:32.336 --> 12:33.712
<i>I'm not seeing anyone.</i>

12:36.882 --> 12:37.883
Hey, Dana.

12:37.925 --> 12:38.884
My typ order.

12:43.388 --> 12:44.556
Thanks.

12:45.057 --> 12:46.058
See you later.

12:48.060 --> 12:48.936
<i>Her?</i>

12:50.062 --> 12:51.230
<i>Hmm.</i>

12:52.439 --> 12:53.774
<i>I'm not seeing it.</i>

12:54.274 --> 12:55.484
See something you like?

12:55.567 --> 12:56.568
Oh.

12:56.652 --> 12:59.238
Word of advice,
careful with that one.

13:00.113 --> 13:02.658
Sugar-coated onion,
if you know what I mean.

13:05.702 --> 13:08.330
What's her um,
what's her name?

13:08.872 --> 13:10.916
Pammy.
Pamela.

13:11.625 --> 13:12.793
I call her, "Pammy."

13:12.918 --> 13:13.752
She hates it.

13:14.753 --> 13:15.963
<i>You're right, we should go.</i>

13:16.088 --> 13:17.130
Shut up.

13:17.256 --> 13:19.132
Sorry, not you, not...

13:19.258 --> 13:20.092
Sorry.

13:36.900 --> 13:38.944
<i>Don't even think about it.</i>

13:39.027 --> 13:40.112
It's not your decision.

13:41.363 --> 13:43.031
<i>You know this never ends well.</i>

13:43.615 --> 13:44.783
What's that supposed to mean?

13:44.867 --> 13:46.785
<i>You know exactly what it means.</i>

13:54.126 --> 13:55.627
<i>Oh, fuck.</i>

14:30.787 --> 14:32.831
<i>I am not doing this again.</i>

14:32.956 --> 14:33.957
Good.

14:34.458 --> 14:35.667
Do this by myself.

14:58.649 --> 14:59.858
Looking for something?

14:59.942 --> 15:00.859
Uh, yes.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.194
I mean, no.

15:02.277 --> 15:04.613
I'm looking around.

15:07.866 --> 15:09.868
You're the guy from the diner
who was staring at my ass.

15:09.993 --> 15:12.371
No. To be fair,
I was looking in your hands.

15:12.496 --> 15:14.164
That's even weirder.

15:14.873 --> 15:16.667
I'm just...

15:17.209 --> 15:19.044
Just looking for a gift.

15:19.086 --> 15:20.170
For who?

15:20.712 --> 15:21.713
For my dad.

15:23.882 --> 15:25.884
Crystal unicorn and earrings.

15:26.552 --> 15:27.719
Fabulous.

15:28.887 --> 15:29.888
Sorry.

15:45.779 --> 15:46.780
Fuck.

15:47.990 --> 15:48.991
Fucked it up.

15:49.074 --> 15:49.992
<i>For the best.</i>

15:50.075 --> 15:51.034
Fucked it up.

16:13.932 --> 16:15.392
So you're new in town.

16:15.934 --> 16:17.728
You plan on staying
in Hackett for a while?

16:17.811 --> 16:19.396
Yeah, yeah, a little,
little while, yeah.

16:19.479 --> 16:21.648
<i>Not too long, I hope.</i>

16:21.732 --> 16:25.569
And you said you have
experience in a stockroom?

16:25.652 --> 16:26.945
Yeah, yes, uh, two--

16:27.029 --> 16:29.198
two different grocery stores,
it should be.

16:29.281 --> 16:30.991
Oh, uh.

16:31.074 --> 16:33.285
Hell, I don't even know why
I bother with all this stuff.

16:33.368 --> 16:35.746
I can't stand paperwork.

16:37.414 --> 16:40.292
Look, you seem like
a nice kid.

16:40.834 --> 16:42.836
You don't have any tattoos
on your face or anything.

16:42.961 --> 16:45.672
And most important, you seem
like you want the job.

16:45.797 --> 16:46.757
Yeah.

16:46.798 --> 16:48.467
Right now, it's just my daughter
and I here,

16:48.509 --> 16:49.801
and the holidays are a bitch.

16:49.885 --> 16:50.969
Pardon my French.

16:51.470 --> 16:52.638
<i>If he only knew.</i>

16:52.721 --> 16:55.516
Um, Pam, Pam,
Pamela's your daughter?

16:56.892 --> 16:57.851
Yeah.

16:58.393 --> 16:59.603
You've met?

17:00.187 --> 17:03.440
Oh, just, uh, just briefly.

17:03.524 --> 17:05.192
We were--
I was shopping upstairs

17:05.275 --> 17:07.361
and sorta chatted.

17:07.903 --> 17:08.862
Like, together?

17:08.946 --> 17:12.491
Uh, talked together, yeah.

17:12.574 --> 17:14.618
I'm a very protective father,
Billy.

17:18.622 --> 17:21.583
Gotcha.

17:21.667 --> 17:23.544
I'm kidding around.

17:23.669 --> 17:25.003
When can you start?

17:25.879 --> 17:27.798
When do you need me?

17:29.341 --> 17:30.551
<i>Dean spoke fondly of you,</i>

17:30.676 --> 17:32.594
said to fix you up
with my best room.

17:32.678 --> 17:33.679
Yeah, he's a nice guy.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.013
He just gave me a job.

17:36.014 --> 17:39.726
You know, we dated for a while
back in '82 before he met Ida.

17:40.519 --> 17:41.395
Yeah.

17:42.354 --> 17:43.730
He's the one that got away.

17:44.398 --> 17:46.400
To be honest,
I was a bit of a slut back then,

17:46.483 --> 17:48.235
so it's no surprise
he chose her.

17:50.612 --> 17:54.408
Anyways, when you find
that special someone,

17:54.491 --> 17:55.659
don't let 'em go.

17:56.535 --> 17:58.162
There we are, room six.

18:06.879 --> 18:07.880
Holy shit.

18:08.672 --> 18:10.883
It's very, very nice.

18:11.592 --> 18:14.261
If, uh, if that toilet
keeps running,

18:14.386 --> 18:15.554
jiggle the flusher.

18:16.054 --> 18:18.724
Oh, and uh, if you have
any other problems,

18:18.765 --> 18:20.142
knock three times on the pipe.

18:20.225 --> 18:21.310
I live right below.

18:21.393 --> 18:22.644
I'm terrible with my mobile.

18:24.938 --> 18:26.523
It's very nice.
Thank you.

18:34.573 --> 18:37.075
<i>What is wrong with this town?</i>

18:37.159 --> 18:39.995
<i>Everyone is so nice.</i>

18:40.662 --> 18:41.872
It's refreshing.

18:43.749 --> 18:45.209
I think staying here
is a good idea.

18:46.752 --> 18:47.753
<i>How long?</i>

18:48.420 --> 18:49.421
I don't know.

18:57.930 --> 18:59.431
<i>Just don't forget who you are</i>

18:59.515 --> 19:01.975
<i>and what you do.</i>

19:14.029 --> 19:20.077
<i>♪ Christmas is a feeling</i>
<i>everybody knows ♪</i>

19:20.786 --> 19:24.289
<i>♪ Brings back</i>
<i>an old man's childhood ♪</i>

19:24.414 --> 19:27.417
<i>♪ Making angels in the snow ♪</i>

19:50.691 --> 19:52.192
- Hey, new guy?
- Yeah.

19:52.276 --> 19:53.485
I need a pre-lit tree,

19:53.569 --> 19:55.571
a box of ornaments,
and an angel, stat.

20:03.120 --> 20:04.413
<i>Well, get to it.</i>

20:16.508 --> 20:17.509
Anything else?

20:17.551 --> 20:18.927
Uh, where's the angel?

20:19.511 --> 20:20.679
Yeah.

20:26.685 --> 20:27.644
What?

20:27.728 --> 20:29.104
Why does the angel
have to go at the top?

20:29.188 --> 20:31.565
Why can't it go like,
anywhere else, like...

20:35.319 --> 20:36.361
...here?

20:36.486 --> 20:37.779
And that looks good to you?

20:38.405 --> 20:39.406
Hmm.

20:39.489 --> 20:40.532
Yeah, I didn't think so,
new guy.

20:41.617 --> 20:42.784
Do this, please.

20:46.705 --> 20:49.208
It's uh, it's Billy.

20:52.044 --> 20:54.004
Billy?
Okay.

20:59.051 --> 21:00.052
Can I call you, "Bill"?

21:00.802 --> 21:02.095
I just feel like I'm talking
to a 5-year-old

21:02.221 --> 21:03.555
when I say Billy.

21:06.225 --> 21:07.726
Sure, yeah, whatever you say...

21:09.102 --> 21:10.020
...Pammy.

21:17.152 --> 21:18.362
Okay, you win.

21:18.445 --> 21:19.530
Billy, it is.

21:27.538 --> 21:29.748
<i>Jesus, here we go again.</i>

21:32.918 --> 21:34.545
Um...

21:34.586 --> 21:36.588
I was just wondering if uh,

21:37.756 --> 21:40.968
would you wanna go for
like coffee with me sometime?

21:41.093 --> 21:42.928
Those are the questions
I prefer to ask.

21:44.263 --> 21:45.681
Unless you're a serial killer.

21:45.764 --> 21:46.849
I'm a True Crime junkie,

21:46.932 --> 21:48.600
and I would have
so many questions.

21:49.184 --> 21:50.143
Oh.

21:50.894 --> 21:52.104
Yeah, no.

21:52.187 --> 21:53.146
Bummer.

21:54.648 --> 21:56.233
<i>She's kind of a weirdo.</i>

21:57.067 --> 21:58.193
Shut up.

22:02.030 --> 22:03.365
Uh, this fucking guy

22:03.448 --> 22:04.741
won't leave me alone.

22:08.453 --> 22:09.371
Fucking...

22:10.080 --> 22:13.458
You're such a motherfucking
stupid piece of shit.

22:13.584 --> 22:15.460
Fucking cunt!

22:21.300 --> 22:22.634
It's fine. I just...

22:23.635 --> 22:24.720
Hey, I got you.

22:24.803 --> 22:26.054
Just keep doing
what you're doing.

22:26.138 --> 22:27.222
I'll grab a broom.

22:29.850 --> 22:30.893
Holy shit.

22:37.691 --> 22:39.568
<i>I'm getting one</i>
<i>of those feelings.</i>

22:40.068 --> 22:41.445
<i>Keep your eyes open.</i>

22:52.956 --> 22:54.333
Yeah, the shop is
looking beautiful.

22:54.458 --> 22:55.834
You ready for Christmas?

22:55.959 --> 22:56.877
George.

22:57.002 --> 22:58.045
And I have to tell you
something.

22:58.170 --> 23:00.506
If I was 35 years younger,
I'd be all over you.

23:02.007 --> 23:03.467
George.

23:03.509 --> 23:06.261
<i>Him. Tonight.</i>

23:06.345 --> 23:07.846
<i>We do him tonight.</i>

23:17.272 --> 23:18.232
Billy.

23:18.982 --> 23:19.900
Billy.

23:21.818 --> 23:23.862
- Are you okay?
- Oh, yeah.

23:23.946 --> 23:25.197
Sorry.

23:25.280 --> 23:26.448
You okay?

23:27.783 --> 23:28.826
I'm sorry.

23:29.827 --> 23:30.702
I'm really embarrassed.

23:30.828 --> 23:33.038
Um, I snap sometimes.

23:33.956 --> 23:38.544
My dad calls it, "EPD,"
explosive personality disorder.

23:39.878 --> 23:41.046
Who's that guy?

23:42.881 --> 23:44.341
Oh, that's George Vilmo.

23:44.383 --> 23:46.552
He's a sweetheart.
He helps at the store sometimes.

23:46.593 --> 23:48.554
I uh, I think
he's a little lonely.

23:49.555 --> 23:50.806
I gotta tell you, Dean,

23:50.889 --> 23:53.892
it's the highlight of my holiday
season every year. Honestly.

23:53.934 --> 23:55.018
Hey, we need to eat.

26:01.228 --> 26:02.312
Naughty.

26:05.315 --> 26:07.401
<i>♪ What a night of cheer</i>
<i>this is ♪</i>

26:07.484 --> 26:10.112
<i>♪ How grand it is</i>
<i>to feel so merry ♪</i>

26:10.195 --> 26:15.242
<i>♪ Life is very gay when people</i>
<i>catch the Christmas fever ♪</i>

26:15.325 --> 26:16.493
<i>♪ On the warmest</i>
<i>winter evening ♪</i>

26:16.535 --> 26:19.538
<i>♪ On the warmest winter</i>
<i>evening of ♪</i>

26:19.663 --> 26:24.376
<i>♪ Evening of the year ♪</i>

26:26.503 --> 26:28.380
<i>Three more days.</i>

27:58.512 --> 27:59.972
She's amazing, isn't she?

28:01.682 --> 28:03.517
She has a real knack
for this sort of thing.

28:04.184 --> 28:05.477
She's very lucky.

28:06.186 --> 28:07.771
What do you mean?

28:07.855 --> 28:10.440
Well, I mean,
I know I look great, son,

28:10.524 --> 28:11.942
but I'm not gonna be
around forever.

28:14.403 --> 28:17.030
One day,
all of this will be hers.

28:27.291 --> 28:28.417
Carry on.

28:32.963 --> 28:34.006
Uh, hey, Agnes.

28:34.047 --> 28:35.340
It's me uh, Billy.

28:35.382 --> 28:36.508
I'm just calling.

28:36.633 --> 28:39.386
It seems we're low on
the woodwicked candles, uh,

28:39.511 --> 28:41.346
the Christmas forest kind.

28:41.430 --> 28:42.681
So if you could send
another box.

28:42.764 --> 28:44.224
PO is 313.

28:44.725 --> 28:45.726
Thanks.

28:47.436 --> 28:48.812
-Hi.
-Hi.

28:48.896 --> 28:50.522
Uh, my sister got called
into work,

28:50.606 --> 28:52.900
so I'm gonna take my nephew
to hockey practice.

28:52.983 --> 28:53.942
You wanna come?

28:54.651 --> 28:55.694
What about the shop?

28:55.777 --> 28:56.945
My dad's gonna be here.

28:58.113 --> 28:59.156
Okay.

29:01.617 --> 29:03.035
-Okay. Yeah.
-Do you wanna go? Yeah?

29:03.952 --> 29:04.870
Okay, let's go.

29:09.041 --> 29:11.668
So your sister, she doesn't
work at the store ever?

29:12.377 --> 29:13.754
No.

29:13.879 --> 29:16.423
It being named after my mom,
it just-- it isn't her thing.

29:20.886 --> 29:23.764
My uh, my mom died
when we were little.

29:23.889 --> 29:26.141
She had a seizure
while she was driving.

29:26.225 --> 29:27.267
Pow.

29:29.436 --> 29:30.604
I'm sorry.

29:31.647 --> 29:33.440
I just think it hurts her
too much to be there.

29:34.775 --> 29:37.528
Pam, Billy, look at this.

29:38.487 --> 29:41.490
Oh, fuck yes.

29:43.951 --> 29:46.578
You're okay with it, right?
The shop and everything?

29:47.246 --> 29:49.873
I mean, I'm the heiress.

29:52.209 --> 29:54.294
It's what my dad wants and uh,

29:54.419 --> 29:56.088
I know it'll make him happy,
so...

29:57.047 --> 29:57.923
What about you?

30:00.759 --> 30:02.344
Kinda been drifting
my whole life,

30:02.427 --> 30:03.762
since I was eight years old.

30:04.847 --> 30:06.014
Yeah, I don't know.

30:06.098 --> 30:09.101
I guess, I think I'm kinda
just ready to settle down,

30:09.184 --> 30:10.686
you know?

30:10.769 --> 30:13.856
Nice house, cute little wife,
couple kids, minivan?

30:16.984 --> 30:18.151
Yeah, why not?

30:21.572 --> 30:22.781
Bowden, tighten up.

30:22.865 --> 30:25.325
You're playing
like fucking garbage.

30:25.868 --> 30:26.910
Lazy fuck.

30:28.078 --> 30:29.037
<i>Her.</i>

30:30.455 --> 30:31.373
Not right now.

30:31.456 --> 30:33.458
<i>Yes, now. Her.</i>

30:34.126 --> 30:35.335
I'm not in the mood.

30:35.460 --> 30:37.337
<i>I don't care. Look at her.</i>

30:37.838 --> 30:39.006
<i>Pink coat.</i>

30:39.131 --> 30:40.090
She has a kid.

30:40.132 --> 30:41.300
<i>Yeah, by the looks of it,</i>

30:41.341 --> 30:42.885
<i>you'd be doing him a favor.</i>

30:47.347 --> 30:48.640
You know Delphine?

30:48.974 --> 30:51.185
-Hm?
-Delphine Anderson?

30:51.351 --> 30:52.644
Pink coat lady.

30:52.728 --> 30:54.313
Oh, no.
No, I don't.

30:54.396 --> 30:55.314
No.

30:57.107 --> 30:59.276
Seems like you want to.
I-- I can introduce you.

30:59.359 --> 31:00.277
Oh, that's okay.

31:00.360 --> 31:01.528
- That's--
- Delphine!

31:02.905 --> 31:05.324
<i>Hm, this will be interesting.</i>

31:05.407 --> 31:06.325
Hey, Pam.

31:06.408 --> 31:07.326
Hey, Del.

31:07.409 --> 31:08.827
I uh, wanna introduce
you to Billy.

31:08.911 --> 31:10.162
He's the new hire at the store.

31:11.246 --> 31:12.414
I see.

31:12.998 --> 31:14.082
Pleased to meet you.

31:17.294 --> 31:19.671
Uh, I'll be right back.

31:24.676 --> 31:27.012
It's okay.
I know what you're thinking.

31:39.733 --> 31:40.734
Hey!

31:44.613 --> 31:45.697
Yo, Tommy.

31:46.281 --> 31:48.617
Tommy, yo, Tommy.
Tommy man.

31:49.284 --> 31:50.619
Stop, stop.

31:54.331 --> 31:55.290
Excuse me.

32:00.712 --> 32:02.005
Stop it.

32:06.385 --> 32:09.054
Liam? Liam, what happened?

32:09.137 --> 32:11.723
They said my stick was for girls
because it was pink

32:11.765 --> 32:13.976
and they said only fags
wear figure skates.

32:14.059 --> 32:16.019
Then they pushed me
and said the Snatcher

32:16.103 --> 32:19.356
would get me, because
the Snatcher looks girly.

32:19.439 --> 32:21.441
God, fuck.
I'm sorry.

32:22.484 --> 32:25.529
Hey, hey, hey! What the hell?

32:27.281 --> 32:28.740
Where were you?

32:28.824 --> 32:30.951
They jumped him
and called him, a "fag."

32:31.034 --> 32:32.911
They're boys.
They're messing around.

32:33.036 --> 32:34.371
Messing--
Oh, they're messing around?

32:34.496 --> 32:35.747
-Mess around with me,
motherfucker.
-Hey, hey.

32:35.873 --> 32:37.749
How about that? Let's go.
I will fuck you up!

32:37.833 --> 32:39.168
Get this bitch out of my barn.

32:39.251 --> 32:40.252
Oh, I'm a bitch?

32:40.377 --> 32:42.462
I'll burn your fucking
house down!

32:46.258 --> 32:47.384
You got any nines?

32:47.426 --> 32:48.594
Go fish.

32:51.471 --> 32:53.432
Is your auntie always like this?

32:53.473 --> 32:56.143
Not always.
Only when she gets mad.

32:57.603 --> 32:59.354
She has always been
a little bit of a pipe bomb.

33:00.814 --> 33:03.901
Sometimes it seems like
there's another person

33:03.984 --> 33:05.068
inside of her.

33:07.654 --> 33:08.906
Who's the Snatcher?

33:08.989 --> 33:10.657
He steals kids.

33:10.741 --> 33:13.577
Liam, there is no Snatcher.

33:15.579 --> 33:19.124
It's just a-- a kind of
an urban legend around here.

33:20.250 --> 33:23.629
Though recently it has felt
a little too close to home.

33:26.298 --> 33:28.967
Couple towns in the county
have had some kids go missing.

33:30.802 --> 33:33.805
But thankfully, yeah, Hackett
hasn't made it up on that wall.

33:56.453 --> 33:57.496
Max.

33:59.289 --> 34:00.290
Hey, Pammy.

34:01.458 --> 34:02.751
What are you doing here?

34:02.835 --> 34:04.127
Well, you know the guys
at the station

34:04.169 --> 34:06.004
uh, we-- we stay in touch so...

34:07.172 --> 34:10.843
They called me and, uh,
got here as soon as I could.

34:19.393 --> 34:22.980
So, um, still doing
this kinda stuff?

34:23.063 --> 34:23.981
Yep.

34:24.565 --> 34:26.900
Beating up kids now?

34:26.984 --> 34:28.151
They deserved it.

34:32.614 --> 34:34.950
Okay, well, uh,
you're free to go.

34:37.870 --> 34:39.037
What do you mean?

34:39.163 --> 34:40.164
You can go.

34:41.665 --> 34:42.833
So you did your cop thing?

34:43.667 --> 34:45.711
Yeah.
Yeah, I did my cop thing.

34:46.545 --> 34:47.546
You're welcome.

34:48.380 --> 34:51.508
Lucky for you the, uh,
parents aren't pressing charges.

34:51.550 --> 34:53.218
Said if the boys did
what you say they did,

34:53.302 --> 34:55.053
then they deserved it, so...

34:56.221 --> 34:57.764
Thank God, there's still
good parenting out there, huh?

34:57.890 --> 34:58.891
Got it.

35:09.193 --> 35:10.277
Look at me.

35:18.494 --> 35:20.078
You're not answering
any of my--

35:20.162 --> 35:21.580
You punched me in the face.

35:21.705 --> 35:23.248
You know I didn't mean to.

35:23.373 --> 35:24.416
It's over.

35:25.375 --> 35:26.877
You don't get a second chance.

35:27.586 --> 35:28.754
Get over it, Max.

36:07.084 --> 36:08.252
I miss you.

36:30.524 --> 36:32.234
- An hour away.
- Oh, wow.

36:32.317 --> 36:34.027
- The Whiteshell?
- Yeah.

36:34.111 --> 36:35.654
- Yeah, the Whiteshell.
- The Whiteshell.

36:35.737 --> 36:37.072
I like going to West Hawk.

36:38.031 --> 36:39.032
Oh.

36:39.116 --> 36:41.743
Tell him about his...

36:42.452 --> 36:43.954
Jesus, sweetheart.

36:47.457 --> 36:49.293
Oh, what the hell
were you thinking?

36:49.334 --> 36:50.711
I'm fine, Dad.
Thanks for asking.

36:50.836 --> 36:51.837
I'm sorry.

36:51.879 --> 36:53.005
<i>Billy...</i>

36:53.046 --> 36:54.381
<i>I'm getting one</i>
<i>of those feelings.</i>

36:54.506 --> 36:55.340
Not now.

36:55.841 --> 36:57.843
<i>Just keep your eyes open.</i>

36:58.552 --> 36:59.511
Hi.

36:59.595 --> 37:02.097
Me and Billy played cards
and I won.

37:02.181 --> 37:03.932
Wow.

37:04.016 --> 37:05.559
Lucky you.

37:07.936 --> 37:09.479
So, did I hear ice cream?

37:09.563 --> 37:10.355
Yeah.

37:10.564 --> 37:11.857
I heard ice cream, too.
We should get ice cream.

37:11.940 --> 37:13.734
Ice cream.

37:32.711 --> 37:34.213
- I really think--
- I wanted to--

37:34.713 --> 37:36.507
-Sorry, you go.
-No, uh...

37:38.050 --> 37:42.054
Thank you very much
for everything today.

37:43.597 --> 37:46.725
Sometimes I feel like that,
um, the anger--

37:46.808 --> 37:47.893
The EPD?

37:48.727 --> 37:52.523
Yes.
I-- I feel like it's an escape.

37:52.606 --> 37:54.024
Like it's the only thing
I have control over.

37:54.107 --> 37:57.236
And I know that that probably
sounds psychotic.

37:57.319 --> 37:58.529
No.

38:03.200 --> 38:04.618
Am I a bad person?

38:04.701 --> 38:05.577
No.

38:06.203 --> 38:08.330
No, I can-- can tell you
right now

38:08.413 --> 38:10.874
that you are definitely
not a bad person.

38:13.752 --> 38:15.921
I almost bit a kid's nose off
in third grade.

38:16.755 --> 38:19.132
You see?
That's what I'm saying.

38:19.258 --> 38:20.133
I know I'm a bad person.

38:20.259 --> 38:21.802
Just doing a bad thing
is different

38:21.927 --> 38:23.470
than being a bad person.

38:24.304 --> 38:25.806
Good people do bad things.

38:25.931 --> 38:27.099
<i>I, uh, hate to break up</i>

38:27.140 --> 38:29.643
<i>the love fest here,</i>
<i>but we gotta get going.</i>

38:31.812 --> 38:33.981
Okay. Your turn.

38:35.315 --> 38:36.942
Mine's not as mushy as yours.

38:37.025 --> 38:38.402
Mushy?
No.

38:38.902 --> 38:40.070
That was not mushy.

38:40.154 --> 38:41.071
Bad person is different

38:41.280 --> 38:42.739
- than doing a bad thing.
- A little mushy, though.

38:42.823 --> 38:44.158
Is that what you just said?

38:44.658 --> 38:45.534
That's mushy.

38:46.910 --> 38:47.953
No.

38:48.078 --> 38:50.747
I hate mushy, so lay it on me.

38:51.540 --> 38:52.749
Okay, here it goes.

38:57.462 --> 38:58.589
Can I borrow your car?

39:01.842 --> 39:03.844
Wow.
Yeah, you're right.

39:03.969 --> 39:06.054
That wasn't mushy.
That was tacky as fuck.

39:06.138 --> 39:08.140
Yeah, it was tacky.
You don't have to give me the--

39:08.182 --> 39:09.516
No, it's fine.
Go for it.

39:11.810 --> 39:14.354
You know, I'm gonna figure out
what's going on in there.

39:15.522 --> 39:16.815
I'm gonna do it.

39:19.568 --> 39:20.777
So what's up?

39:20.861 --> 39:22.654
You got a hot date
with Delphine?

39:22.738 --> 39:25.991
Oh, yeah.
You, uh-- You have no idea.

39:35.167 --> 39:36.585
How far is this place?

39:36.668 --> 39:37.961
<i>Just keep on this road.</i>

39:38.003 --> 39:39.296
<i>We're getting warmer.</i>

39:41.465 --> 39:42.508
I've been driving for,
like, an hour.

39:44.676 --> 39:49.681
<i>♪ So let us have</i>
<i>a very merry Christmas ♪</i>

39:50.682 --> 39:54.311
<i>♪ Good love and joy</i>
<i>and good wishes ♪</i>

39:54.394 --> 39:56.188
What is going on here?

39:58.690 --> 40:01.610
<i>Yeah. Let's scope it out first.</i>

40:02.778 --> 40:05.364
<i>♪ A very merry Christmas </i>

40:11.995 --> 40:13.163
You packing, Santa?

40:21.213 --> 40:22.256
You're good to go.

40:29.096 --> 40:30.430
<i>♪ Santa is my bitch </i>

40:30.556 --> 40:32.140
<i>♪ And I tell him</i>
<i>where the party at ♪</i>

40:32.224 --> 40:33.392
<i>♪ I'm gonna get my wish ♪</i>

40:33.433 --> 40:35.394
<i>♪ When I'm sitting</i>
<i>on your daddy ass ♪</i>

40:35.435 --> 40:36.436
<i>♪ I do what I want ♪</i>

40:36.520 --> 40:38.397
<i>♪ So then fuck getting famous ♪</i>

40:38.480 --> 40:39.398
<i>♪ Jingle on your boots ♪</i>

40:39.481 --> 40:41.525
<i>♪ So I'm motherfucking famous ♪</i>

40:41.608 --> 40:44.695
<i>This I did not expect.</i>

40:44.778 --> 40:48.949
Let's just find her
and get this over with.

40:49.032 --> 40:50.033
<i>Agreed.</i>

40:50.534 --> 40:53.579
<i>We are pilgrims in</i>
<i>an unholy land.</i>

41:09.261 --> 41:10.596
Hello?

41:12.264 --> 41:13.599
Hello, everyone.

41:15.267 --> 41:18.228
First off, I wanna thank you all
for coming out tonight.

41:18.854 --> 41:20.522
This is the third annual

41:20.606 --> 41:24.276
I'm Dreaming of
a White Power Christmas party.

41:26.695 --> 41:28.906
I know, right?
Heil!

41:28.989 --> 41:30.616
Heil!

41:31.408 --> 41:32.659
Tonight is the night

41:32.743 --> 41:35.704
where we get to show
our true colors,

41:36.413 --> 41:38.916
who we really are inside.

41:39.458 --> 41:41.293
Something the world
makes us hide.

41:41.919 --> 41:44.630
makes us feel shame.

41:45.631 --> 41:48.300
We shouldn't have to feel shame
for what we believe,

41:48.800 --> 41:52.054
for wanting a better America
for our children.

41:52.638 --> 41:56.975
No, tonight we remind ourselves

41:57.017 --> 42:00.187
that Christmas is still
a white Christian holiday

42:00.270 --> 42:03.565
that no one can take away
from us.

42:04.525 --> 42:08.570
So, grab a drink,
make out with someone

42:08.654 --> 42:13.742
under the mistletoe,
and have some fucking fun.

42:14.451 --> 42:15.661
Heil!

42:19.248 --> 42:21.625
<i>Okay. So, what are we thinking?</i>

42:21.667 --> 42:24.294
<i>Stakeout?</i>
<i>Wait for her to use the john?</i>

42:24.837 --> 42:26.672
No.
We kill 'em all.

42:26.797 --> 42:28.215
<i>Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold on.</i>

42:28.340 --> 42:29.550
<i>Let's talk about this.</i>

42:32.010 --> 42:33.512
Nothing to talk about.

42:33.554 --> 42:35.013
<i>For Christ's sake,</i>

42:35.055 --> 42:36.557
<i>at least get a gun.</i>

42:37.182 --> 42:38.433
Guns are for pussies.

42:43.063 --> 42:45.148
Hey, Santa,
you want me to check that out--

43:20.559 --> 43:23.520
<i>♪ So exciting to know</i>
<i>he's near ♪</i>

43:23.604 --> 43:27.608
<i>♪ Can hardly wait,</i>
<i>he's almost here ♪</i>

43:29.776 --> 43:32.362
<i>♪ Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>he's looking for you ♪</i>

43:33.614 --> 43:36.200
<i>♪ Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>what you gonna do? ♪</i>

43:36.867 --> 43:39.745
<i>♪ Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>he's got a surprise ♪</i>

43:39.828 --> 43:42.080
<i>♪ Tomorrow comes ♪</i>

43:42.206 --> 43:44.917
<i>♪ You won't believe your eyes ♪</i>

43:51.924 --> 43:54.051
<i>♪ These bells, they say jingle</i>
<i>and sway ♪</i>

44:04.102 --> 44:06.772
<i>♪ And a sound </i>

44:06.855 --> 44:10.984
<i>♪ Of a sleigh rider,</i>
<i>he's looking for you ♪</i>

44:11.693 --> 44:14.988
<i>♪ Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>what you gonna do? ♪</i>

44:15.072 --> 44:18.033
<i>♪ Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>he's got a surprise ♪</i>

44:19.535 --> 44:21.119
What the shit?

44:56.405 --> 45:01.201
<i>♪ Oh, he's a sleigh rider,</i>
<i>he's looking for you ♪</i>

45:02.995 --> 45:05.455
♪ <i>Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>what you gonna do? ♪</i>

45:05.998 --> 45:09.001
<i>♪ Sleigh rider,</i>
<i>he's got a surprise ♪</i>

45:09.126 --> 45:11.211
<i>♪ Tomorrow comes ♪</i>

45:11.336 --> 45:14.548
<i>♪ You won't believe your eyes ♪</i>

45:23.348 --> 45:24.516
Oh, shit.

45:28.228 --> 45:29.271
God.

45:33.484 --> 45:34.401
<i>Don't worry, kid.</i>

45:36.612 --> 45:38.071
<i>I know where she's going.</i>

46:09.353 --> 46:10.562
Punish.

47:38.442 --> 47:39.526
Fuck.

47:41.403 --> 47:43.572
Oh, fuck!

48:15.729 --> 48:17.397
<i>We almost died tonight.</i>

48:18.398 --> 48:20.234
Yeah, but we didn't.

48:20.317 --> 48:22.945
<i>It was reckless. Stupid.</i>

48:24.613 --> 48:25.781
You wanted me to keep going?

48:25.864 --> 48:27.658
<i>Yeah, with a gun.</i>

48:28.617 --> 48:30.118
I'm sorry, I have principles.

48:30.202 --> 48:31.703
<i>Principles, my ass.</i>

48:31.787 --> 48:33.455
<i>That was about control.</i>

48:33.539 --> 48:35.791
<i>You just wanted</i>
<i>to do it your way.</i>

48:36.375 --> 48:39.878
Yeah, fine.
Maybe you're right.

48:40.879 --> 48:42.381
<i>Uh, look...</i>

48:42.506 --> 48:45.551
<i>just don't wanna see</i>
<i>you get killed.</i>

48:47.052 --> 48:48.095
Oh, fuck!

48:50.222 --> 48:51.265
Oh, fuck.

48:51.390 --> 48:53.892
<i>Hmm, good luck with that one.</i>

49:04.319 --> 49:07.656
Okay, good choice.
Okay.

49:08.824 --> 49:12.077
Merry Christmas and take care.

49:12.161 --> 49:13.579
Sorry, I'm late.

49:13.662 --> 49:17.374
Oh, thank God you're here.
What happened to your face?

49:17.416 --> 49:18.417
What?

49:18.500 --> 49:21.003
Your f--
You know what?

49:21.086 --> 49:23.964
It's none of my business.
Uh, I'm sorry.

49:24.089 --> 49:25.716
I have a bit of a problem.

49:25.757 --> 49:26.925
What's up?

49:26.967 --> 49:28.385
Santa didn't show.

49:28.427 --> 49:30.012
George was supposed
to be here like an hour ago,

49:30.095 --> 49:31.430
and I've called him,
and I've called him.

49:31.471 --> 49:33.515
I even asked Claire from the
bakery to go down to his house,

49:33.599 --> 49:36.268
-and there's no answer there.
-Sorry, this, um George...

49:36.310 --> 49:38.103
George, the guy
that you were talking to

49:38.187 --> 49:39.104
the other day?

49:39.229 --> 49:41.356
George Vilmo. He does Santa
for us every year.

49:42.024 --> 49:43.025
Could your dad do it?

49:43.108 --> 49:44.443
No. Not gonna happen.

49:44.526 --> 49:45.819
Not since the pooping incident.

49:46.361 --> 49:47.446
Pooping incident?

49:47.946 --> 49:49.031
Can you do it?

49:49.823 --> 49:51.867
I would appreciate it greatly,
son.

49:52.618 --> 49:54.620
<i>No. Tell her no.</i>

49:54.703 --> 49:56.622
I know it's not your job,
but it would mean a lot,

49:56.747 --> 49:58.081
especially to me.

49:58.123 --> 49:59.291
<i>Billy, you put that suit on</i>

49:59.416 --> 50:01.752
<i>head to toe,</i>
<i>you're gonna lose control.</i>

50:04.630 --> 50:05.631
Where's the suit?

50:05.672 --> 50:06.965
Oh, thank you, Billy.

50:08.509 --> 50:10.594
Okay, it's in the back office.

50:10.636 --> 50:12.554
Do you, uh, do you know
what you're doing?

50:12.638 --> 50:14.139
I assume you've never been
Santa before.

50:15.390 --> 50:16.558
Uh...

50:20.562 --> 50:21.730
<i>What are you doing?</i>

50:22.397 --> 50:23.565
I got this.

50:23.649 --> 50:25.234
<i>This is more powerful</i>
<i>than you know.</i>

50:25.317 --> 50:27.319
<i>Trust me,</i>
<i>I have been here before.</i>

50:27.402 --> 50:28.487
I'm not you.

51:00.060 --> 51:02.312
Okay, who's excited
to meet Santa?

51:04.857 --> 51:06.900
<i>Jesus, this is gonna be bad.</i>

51:08.110 --> 51:10.028
Ah! That's it.

51:10.612 --> 51:12.197
Okay, Celia,
look over here, baby.

51:12.281 --> 51:13.740
Smile.
Ooh.

51:35.220 --> 51:36.430
<i>Billy, listen to me.</i>

51:37.097 --> 51:39.266
<i>You're not going to kill</i>
<i>this little girl.</i>

51:39.391 --> 51:42.728
<i>You hear me?</i>
<i>That's not what Billy would do.</i>

51:44.146 --> 51:45.397
<i>Billy, Billy.</i>

51:45.981 --> 51:48.108
<i>I need you to forget</i>
<i>what you are.</i>

51:48.942 --> 51:52.446
<i>Forget what you do.</i>
<i>Do exactly what I say, okay?</i>

51:53.155 --> 51:57.826
<i>Just follow me, buddy.</i>
<i>Follow me.</i>

52:00.162 --> 52:02.164
<i>Hello, little girl.</i>
<i>What's your name?</i>

52:03.373 --> 52:04.750
So, what's your name?

52:04.875 --> 52:05.834
Celia.

52:05.918 --> 52:07.419
<i>What a pretty name.</i>

52:07.503 --> 52:08.629
<i>Tell me, Celia,</i>

52:09.421 --> 52:11.548
<i>have you been a good girl</i>
<i>this year?</i>

52:12.424 --> 52:13.467
You been a good girl

52:13.592 --> 52:14.635
this year, Celia?

52:14.760 --> 52:17.846
Yes, well, except this one time.

52:17.930 --> 52:21.016
I was mad at my mom,
and I throw a banana at her,

52:21.099 --> 52:22.267
but I said sorry.

52:22.351 --> 52:24.561
<i>Oh, I am so happy to hear that.</i>

52:25.103 --> 52:27.064
<i>Is there something special</i>
<i>you'd like for Christmas?</i>

52:27.606 --> 52:28.941
A pink skateboard.

52:29.483 --> 52:32.486
<i>Oh, boy. You're a skater?</i>

52:32.986 --> 52:34.112
Yeah.

52:34.196 --> 52:35.280
And, uh,

52:35.364 --> 52:36.782
what about we get you
a helmet,

52:36.865 --> 52:39.451
so you don't dent
that noggin of yours?

52:39.535 --> 52:40.953
A pink one?

52:41.036 --> 52:42.371
<i>A pink one.</i>

52:46.750 --> 52:48.919
Merry Christmas.

52:48.961 --> 52:51.296
<i>Uh, you got it from here, kid.</i>

52:51.338 --> 52:52.464
<i>You can do this.</i>

52:53.632 --> 52:54.633
He's pretty good.

52:56.301 --> 52:57.636
Yeah, he's um...

52:59.471 --> 53:01.473
-Yeah, nice, you know.
-Mmhmm.

53:08.689 --> 53:10.816
Santa, what happened
to your face?

53:10.899 --> 53:15.737
Oh, um, Rudolph got
a little frisky last night.

53:19.741 --> 53:20.909
He's so sweet.

53:23.162 --> 53:24.746
I remember taking you to Santa.

53:31.170 --> 53:32.004
<i>Kid...</i>

53:32.171 --> 53:34.131
<i>I'm getting one</i>
<i>of those feelings again.</i>

53:34.173 --> 53:35.549
Not now, Charlie.

53:35.674 --> 53:37.342
<i>I know, I know. I just--</i>

53:37.384 --> 53:38.677
I said not fucking now.

53:39.845 --> 53:41.555
<i>Just scan the crowd quick.</i>

53:54.193 --> 53:55.861
So what do you want
for Christmas, bud?

53:55.944 --> 53:56.945
A bike.

54:12.377 --> 54:13.420
Thank you.

54:15.380 --> 54:16.507
<i>Sure.</i>

54:19.760 --> 54:21.428
What?
What's wrong?

54:21.553 --> 54:22.888
<i>Do I need to remind you</i>

54:22.971 --> 54:24.223
<i>what we do again?</i>

54:25.390 --> 54:26.558
I'm aware.

54:26.642 --> 54:28.602
<i>And what happens if we don't?</i>

54:32.314 --> 54:33.440
<i>Say it.</i>

54:34.608 --> 54:35.651
I don't wanna say it.

54:36.944 --> 54:38.695
<i>Let's say it together then.</i>

54:38.779 --> 54:39.780
I don't wanna say it together.

54:39.863 --> 54:41.824
<i>Fine, then I'll say it.</i>

54:43.200 --> 54:46.703
<i>Someone else dies,</i>
<i>and we don't get to choose.</i>

54:47.329 --> 54:49.164
<i>You wanna talk about control,</i>
<i>bub?</i>

54:49.248 --> 54:53.252
<i>Who would you rather it be?</i>
<i>A Nazi or a nine-year-old girl?</i>

54:53.335 --> 54:54.586
<i>A killer or a mom with a--</i>

54:54.628 --> 54:56.964
Yeah, I get it.
I fucking get it.

54:57.089 --> 54:59.216
<i>I don't think you do.</i>

54:59.758 --> 55:01.426
<i>Now's not the time to break</i>

55:01.468 --> 55:03.428
<i>a perfect</i>
<i>10 year killing streak.</i>

55:11.937 --> 55:12.980
<i>You hear what I said?</i>

55:13.063 --> 55:14.189
Shh.

55:16.984 --> 55:18.152
Hello?

55:22.406 --> 55:23.282
Hello?

55:53.353 --> 55:54.730
Wait, wait.

56:18.462 --> 56:22.341
Wait, wait, wait.
Keep it on.

56:57.668 --> 56:58.877
I wanna stay with you.

57:02.381 --> 57:03.715
I wanna go where you go.

57:11.557 --> 57:12.891
I made you something.

57:29.324 --> 57:30.409
You like it?

57:31.994 --> 57:32.911
How'd you...

57:34.746 --> 57:36.039
I learned from the best.

57:39.543 --> 57:41.712
See, the angel can go
anywhere she wants.

57:45.257 --> 57:46.425
That's cheesy as fuck.

57:48.260 --> 57:49.428
I worked hard on that.

57:51.930 --> 57:52.931
It's beautiful.

57:55.934 --> 58:01.899
<i>♪ Yeah, this is the time</i>
<i>for love and care ♪</i>

58:08.906 --> 58:10.741
Dad!
We're here.

58:11.909 --> 58:13.619
Will you put this
in the kitchen, please?

58:14.786 --> 58:15.746
Ugh.

58:16.872 --> 58:17.915
Go, go.

58:22.294 --> 58:26.465
<i>♪ This time of the year ♪</i>

58:29.635 --> 58:31.970
<i>♪ This time </i>

58:33.472 --> 58:35.140
Ugh, what died in here?

58:37.059 --> 58:39.645
<i>♪ Of the year </i>

58:39.728 --> 58:41.814
Hey, come help me out in here.

58:41.897 --> 58:44.149
Xavier, will you put
that thing down, please?

59:25.315 --> 59:26.567
When was the last time

59:26.650 --> 59:27.526
you saw him?

59:27.609 --> 59:29.653
Uh, just the other day.

59:29.736 --> 59:31.196
He was-- he was-- he was here.

59:31.280 --> 59:33.991
He was-- he was in the store.

59:34.491 --> 59:35.868
They found George.

59:35.951 --> 59:37.119
We were-- we were talking...

59:37.202 --> 59:39.288
His daughter and grandson,
they--

59:39.371 --> 59:42.666
They found his body.
He was murdered.

59:48.088 --> 59:50.048
<i>And that's not even</i>
<i>the craziest part.</i>

59:51.884 --> 59:56.889
They found Gail, his wife,
rolled up in a rug,

59:58.557 --> 01:00:01.059
<i>tucked away in a crawl space</i>
<i>in his basement.</i>

01:00:05.772 --> 01:00:07.566
They said he murdered her.

01:00:10.319 --> 01:00:12.029
Stabbed her to death.

01:00:12.529 --> 01:00:14.490
I talked to him all the time.
I--

01:00:15.949 --> 01:00:20.871
He-- he was-- he was so sweet.
I-- I thought I knew him.

01:00:31.089 --> 01:00:32.758
Who's that over there?

01:00:32.883 --> 01:00:34.092
It really makes you wonder.

01:00:35.427 --> 01:00:37.679
Uh, that's, uh, that's Billy.

01:00:38.305 --> 01:00:39.681
Who else you know who could be--

01:00:39.765 --> 01:00:41.433
- He's new.
- Hiding something so evil...

01:00:41.475 --> 01:00:42.601
He's a good kid.

01:00:42.643 --> 01:00:43.811
In plain sight?

01:00:48.148 --> 01:00:49.775
When did you last see Mr. Vilmo?

01:00:53.445 --> 01:00:54.488
Let's see.

01:00:54.571 --> 01:00:58.909
Uh, started work here
on the 20th, so, uh...

01:01:00.369 --> 01:01:01.703
So, yeah, the-- the 20th.

01:01:01.787 --> 01:01:02.955
And you spoke with him?

01:01:03.038 --> 01:01:04.122
No.

01:01:04.206 --> 01:01:05.374
I didn't interact with him.

01:01:05.457 --> 01:01:06.959
I just saw him.

01:01:07.459 --> 01:01:08.961
Where are you from, Bill?

01:01:09.586 --> 01:01:11.505
Bar-- Baraboo, Wisconsin.

01:01:11.630 --> 01:01:13.465
Oh, yeah. Circus Museum.

01:01:13.507 --> 01:01:14.800
I got family in Milwaukee.

01:01:14.925 --> 01:01:15.968
That's great.

01:01:16.510 --> 01:01:18.720
How long you been in Hackett?

01:01:20.305 --> 01:01:21.890
Few days.

01:01:21.974 --> 01:01:23.809
Ah.
A few?

01:01:23.851 --> 01:01:24.977
Three? Five?

01:01:25.018 --> 01:01:26.186
Three.

01:01:26.687 --> 01:01:27.563
Ah.

01:01:28.147 --> 01:01:29.356
How'd you get that?

01:01:29.439 --> 01:01:30.357
What?

01:01:30.440 --> 01:01:31.358
The shiner.

01:01:31.441 --> 01:01:32.943
Oh, a box.

01:01:36.405 --> 01:01:37.823
I work in the stockroom.

01:01:37.906 --> 01:01:39.533
Pulled down a box,
it came down and went...

01:01:40.742 --> 01:01:42.452
Got me pretty good, so.

01:01:44.163 --> 01:01:45.497
I think we're good here, Bill.

01:01:45.622 --> 01:01:47.124
Uh, thanks for taking the time.

01:01:47.499 --> 01:01:48.959
Oh, hey.

01:01:49.001 --> 01:01:50.836
You happen to know
a Delphine Anderson, do you?

01:01:51.962 --> 01:01:53.005
Delphine?

01:01:53.130 --> 01:01:57.050
Um, no, no, not--
not off the top of my head.

01:02:02.181 --> 01:02:03.348
Hm.

01:02:05.851 --> 01:02:07.853
<i>The noose is tightening.</i>

01:02:09.730 --> 01:02:11.690
<i>They're gonna figure it out.</i>

01:02:11.773 --> 01:02:13.442
<i>There are cops everywhere,</i>

01:02:13.525 --> 01:02:16.153
<i>and you missed a fucking day</i>
<i>in the book.</i>

01:02:18.155 --> 01:02:23.952
Yeah.
But nothing happened.

01:02:31.168 --> 01:02:32.544
<i>You saw that new missing child</i>

01:02:32.628 --> 01:02:33.879
<i>photo at the store?</i>

01:02:34.004 --> 01:02:35.047
Unrelated.

01:02:35.088 --> 01:02:36.089
<i>You're wrong,</i>

01:02:36.215 --> 01:02:37.716
<i>and you know you're wrong.</i>

01:02:37.758 --> 01:02:40.552
<i>I hate to break it to you, pal,</i>
<i>but we've got to get out of town</i>

01:02:40.594 --> 01:02:42.888
<i>and find someone to kill</i>
<i>tonight,</i>

01:02:44.056 --> 01:02:46.058
<i>or you're going to miss</i>
<i>another day</i>

01:02:46.099 --> 01:02:49.228
<i>and someone who wasn't</i>
<i>supposed to die, will die.</i>

01:02:49.728 --> 01:02:51.563
Innocent people die every day,
Charlie.

01:02:51.647 --> 01:02:52.898
<i>Hm.</i>

01:02:52.981 --> 01:02:55.359
<i>What happens when it's</i>
<i>someone you know?</i>

01:02:55.442 --> 01:02:58.987
<i>Someone you care about?</i>
<i>And you could've stopped it.</i>

01:03:00.113 --> 01:03:02.825
<i>This town is fucked up,</i>
<i>and I know it--</i>

01:03:02.908 --> 01:03:05.244
The whole world is fucked up,
Charlie,

01:03:05.327 --> 01:03:07.246
and I can't do anything
about it.

01:03:07.871 --> 01:03:10.082
I didn't want this.
I didn't choose this.

01:03:11.583 --> 01:03:13.418
I got a taste
of something different,

01:03:15.254 --> 01:03:17.756
something good, something real.

01:03:19.591 --> 01:03:24.930
Being Santa for those kids
being with Pam.

01:03:26.473 --> 01:03:27.599
That's what I want.

01:03:29.143 --> 01:03:30.477
Did you say something?

01:03:32.938 --> 01:03:34.022
No.

01:03:43.365 --> 01:03:45.159
This episode is fucked up.

01:03:46.076 --> 01:03:47.327
<i>As newspapers realize</i>

01:03:47.411 --> 01:03:48.579
<i>that there's a strangler</i>

01:03:48.620 --> 01:03:50.122
<i>on the loose,</i>
<i>the story becomes--</i>

01:03:50.247 --> 01:03:51.748
<i>What happens when she finds out</i>

01:03:51.790 --> 01:03:52.958
<i>what you do?</i>

01:03:53.083 --> 01:03:54.293
<i>There's this entity</i>

01:03:54.418 --> 01:03:55.711
<i>committing these crimes...</i>

01:04:12.227 --> 01:04:14.688
You know what?
Fuck it.

01:04:27.576 --> 01:04:30.662
<i>♪ Silent night </i>

01:04:32.664 --> 01:04:34.249
♪ <i>Holy night ♪</i>

01:04:37.294 --> 01:04:44.134
<i>♪ All is calm</i>
<i>All is bright ♪</i>

01:04:46.678 --> 01:04:53.060
<i>♪ Round yon Virgin</i>
<i>Mother and Child ♪</i>

01:04:55.187 --> 01:04:56.438
Someone there?

01:04:56.522 --> 01:05:03.487
<i>♪ Holy infant so tender</i>
<i>and mild ♪</i>

01:05:05.489 --> 01:05:11.870
<i>♪ Sleep in heavenly peace </i>

01:05:16.708 --> 01:05:18.377
Jesus!

01:05:19.378 --> 01:05:20.546
Oh, my God. Son!

01:05:20.587 --> 01:05:22.756
I'll get you out, so don't--
don't-- don't worry.

01:05:22.881 --> 01:05:25.217
I'll get you-- I'll get you out.
I'll get you out.

01:05:31.723 --> 01:05:32.975
Okay, don't you worry, Tommy.

01:05:33.058 --> 01:05:34.893
I'm gonna, I'm gonna call
for help, okay?

01:05:36.103 --> 01:05:38.313
I'm gonna get you out,
I'm gonna call for help.

01:05:41.817 --> 01:05:42.901
I know, son.

01:05:47.614 --> 01:05:53.537
<i>♪ Sleep in heavenly peace ♪</i>

01:06:08.635 --> 01:06:13.098
<i>♪ Silent night </i>

01:06:13.140 --> 01:06:17.811
<i>♪ Holy night ♪</i>

01:06:17.936 --> 01:06:22.316
<i>♪ Son of God ♪</i>

01:06:22.399 --> 01:06:27.446
<i>♪ Love's pure light ♪</i>

01:06:27.529 --> 01:06:31.200
<i>♪ Radiant beams ♪</i>

01:06:31.283 --> 01:06:36.121
<i>♪ From Thy holy face ♪</i>

01:06:37.039 --> 01:06:40.626
<i>♪ With the dawn </i>

01:06:40.751 --> 01:06:45.964
<i>♪ Of redeeming grace ♪</i>

01:06:46.632 --> 01:06:50.636
<i>♪ Jesus Lord, at Thy birth </i>

01:06:50.677 --> 01:06:56.975
<i>♪ At Thy birth ♪</i>

01:06:58.310 --> 01:07:04.525
<i>♪ Jesus Lord at Thy birth </i>

01:07:28.841 --> 01:07:32.010
<i>Billy, look up. Look up.</i>

01:07:41.895 --> 01:07:43.522
<i>I wish Santa was real.</i>

01:07:48.652 --> 01:07:49.736
<i>Why?</i>

01:07:51.446 --> 01:07:53.073
So I could get
my Christmas wish.

01:08:32.946 --> 01:08:36.575
I'd only ask for one thing

01:08:37.367 --> 01:08:39.578
for the person who did this,

01:08:42.039 --> 01:08:48.253
so he could watch me
slowly cut him

01:08:49.755 --> 01:08:53.759
into itty-bitty pieces.

01:09:07.147 --> 01:09:08.524
Do you trust me?

01:09:11.401 --> 01:09:12.569
Why?

01:09:12.653 --> 01:09:14.822
<i>This is a bad idea.</i>

01:09:17.032 --> 01:09:20.702
Um, what if I told you--

01:09:20.786 --> 01:09:22.120
<i>You tell her,</i>

01:09:22.246 --> 01:09:24.456
<i>and you're going to lose her.</i>

01:09:24.540 --> 01:09:26.208
What if I told you that--

01:09:30.462 --> 01:09:32.130
What if I told you that
I could make your wish

01:09:32.172 --> 01:09:33.131
come true?

01:09:38.470 --> 01:09:39.638
How?

01:09:40.806 --> 01:09:41.974
Who's the Snatcher?

01:09:43.183 --> 01:09:44.810
He steals kids.

01:09:49.064 --> 01:09:50.440
We got him?

01:09:50.524 --> 01:09:51.775
<i>I got him.</i>

01:10:03.829 --> 01:10:05.122
<i>When I was eight years old,</i>

01:10:05.164 --> 01:10:07.833
<i>my parents were murdered</i>
<i>in front of me.</i>

01:10:07.958 --> 01:10:09.668
Geoffrey!

01:10:09.793 --> 01:10:11.503
<i>By a man dressed</i>

01:10:11.587 --> 01:10:12.671
<i>as Santa Clause.</i>

01:10:12.796 --> 01:10:13.672
Hey!

01:10:18.343 --> 01:10:20.554
Turns out that man
was the janitor

01:10:20.679 --> 01:10:22.181
at my grandfather's hospice.

01:10:27.019 --> 01:10:31.607
<i>I just remember being... scared.</i>

01:10:33.108 --> 01:10:35.569
But also mesmerized.

01:10:35.652 --> 01:10:38.655
You know, like--
like he was drawing me in.

01:10:39.698 --> 01:10:41.116
That's when I felt it.

01:10:53.879 --> 01:10:56.048
Charlie's been with me
ever since that day.

01:10:56.882 --> 01:10:57.883
<i>Wake up, kid.</i>

01:11:01.386 --> 01:11:02.721
So-- so you...

01:11:04.556 --> 01:11:05.808
You're a serial killer?

01:11:05.891 --> 01:11:08.310
I wish it was that easy.

01:11:11.396 --> 01:11:13.273
<i>And nobody wanted to adopt a kid</i>

01:11:13.357 --> 01:11:14.650
<i>with an imaginary friend</i>

01:11:14.733 --> 01:11:17.778
<i>telling him to kill people</i>
<i>at Christmastime.</i>

01:11:19.655 --> 01:11:21.240
Only at Christmas?

01:11:21.323 --> 01:11:24.159
Yeah, the-- the advent calendar,
24 days of Christmas.

01:11:27.704 --> 01:11:30.749
I-- I didn't kill anyone
until I was 17 years old.

01:11:33.418 --> 01:11:35.796
<i>Until Charlie felt</i>
<i>that I was ready.</i>

01:11:35.921 --> 01:11:38.257
<i>She needs to be punished.</i>

01:11:39.299 --> 01:11:40.592
<i>The first person I killed</i>

01:11:40.717 --> 01:11:42.761
<i>was my last foster mom.</i>

01:11:44.596 --> 01:11:46.265
<i>She would drug us.</i>

01:11:47.474 --> 01:11:49.101
Breakfast!

01:11:49.143 --> 01:11:50.352
<i>And wait for us all</i>

01:11:50.435 --> 01:11:52.104
<i>to fall asleep.</i>

01:11:55.149 --> 01:11:57.609
<i>Then lock the doors</i>
<i>and go off for the day.</i>

01:11:59.403 --> 01:12:00.863
<i>The drugging wasn't</i>
<i>the half of it.</i>

01:12:01.613 --> 01:12:04.032
<i>If you broke something</i>
<i>in her perfect house,</i>

01:12:05.742 --> 01:12:07.202
<i>the punishment</i>
<i>would be the same.</i>

01:12:13.125 --> 01:12:14.084
It's okay.

01:12:15.252 --> 01:12:16.295
<i>And the scariest part was</i>

01:12:16.420 --> 01:12:18.088
<i>you never knew</i>
<i>when it was gonna come.</i>

01:12:29.808 --> 01:12:32.144
<i>Three died under her watch.</i>

01:12:33.312 --> 01:12:35.105
<i>All accidents.</i>

01:12:35.189 --> 01:12:37.524
<i>All while she was collecting</i>
<i>thousands from the state.</i>

01:12:38.525 --> 01:12:39.526
<i>She had to go.</i>

01:12:43.071 --> 01:12:47.659
<i>♪ Ho, ho, ho and a-here we go</i>
